  "rationale": "<p>Choice C is correct. Using the distributive property to multiply the terms in the parentheses yields <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"open parenthesis, 2 x cubed, times x cubed, close parenthesis, plus, open parenthesis, 2 x cubed, times negative 2 x, close parenthesis, plus, open parenthesis, 3 x times x cubed, close parenthesis, plus, open parenthesis, 3 x times negative 2 x, close parenthesis\"></span>, which is equivalent to <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"2 x to the sixth power minus 4 x to the fourth power, plus 3 x to the fourth power, minus 6 x squared\"></span>. Combining like terms results in&nbsp; <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"2 x to the sixth power minus x to the fourth power, minus 6 x squared\"></span>.<p>Choices A and D are incorrect and may result from conceptual errors when multiplying the terms in the given expression. Choice B is incorrect and may result from adding, instead of multiplying, <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"open parenthesis, 2 x cubed, plus 3 x, close parenthesis \"></span> and <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"open parenthesis, x cubed, minus 2 x, close parenthesis\"></span>.</p></p>\n",
